<Author>Embarcadero1
<Content>Great small hotel with personal service I stayed here for 9 nights in late July while I was in Madrid for business. It's a deluxe, small hotel with very good, personalized service. The room was very comfortable and the bath included a tub with jacuzzi. Very nice for relaxing after a long day of work. The bed and linens were very, ver ynice. I also appreciated the blackout curtains and small sitting area. The hotel staff left a bottle of sherry twice during my stay - a very nice touch. I did not eat in the restaurant, but did have some room service, which was quite nice. There is a small bar which is really just a waiting area for the restaurant. I was able to have a beer and read the paper outside in the restaurant before they started seating people at 9. The front desk staff are fantastic. They were quick with suggestions, very helpful at every opportunity and always made me feel welcome. The service was one of the best parts of my stay and is the main reason I would go back. I liked that it was on a quiet side street in a residential area. This was part of the reason I chose to stay here. I was a 10 minute subway ride from where I was working. I was willing to give up a fantastic view for quiet. It's in a wealthy neighborhood with lots of embassies. It felt very, very safe. I walked to Chueca (and good food) in 10 minutes. The hotel does have a few drawbacks. There was no desk in my room , which meant I had to put my laptop on the dresser. They haven't quite worked out how to provide internet services either. They should just give away wifi rather than wasting so much time (mine and their staff's) trying to sell it. Other than these glitches, the hotel was very good. I give it a solid 4 stars. To get 5, they would have to improve their rooms and facilities (access to a gym would be a help). I would definitely stay here if when I go back to Madrid. 
