<Author>pamperednyc
<Content>Off the beaten path Beautiful hotel in historic building. Nice sized room that was clean and well equipped. Front desk was very friendly and tried to be helpful however it seemed as if they are more used to business travellers than tourists as they weren't that well versed on basic tourist attractions and/or hot new restaurants, etc. If you know where you want to go and what you want to do, then this wouldn't be an issue. No true concierge per se. Hotel is in a quiet residential area that is only a 5 -10 minute walk to an area filled with restaurants, shopping and tourist attractions, however it is somewhat off the beaten track. Great breakfast (although pricey), friendly and clean in general. Extremely charming appeal. Overall a good hotel despite the above critiques. I'd probably try someplace else next time but would stay here again if nothing else seemed appealing. 
