<Content>Classic, comfortable, friendly Stayed here in summer 2005 - horrifically high temperatures, and the hotel was a welcome refuge to come back to. Traditionally furnished but very comfortable. Staff very friendly and very helpful - even when we arrived for check-in hours before normal time. Really good breakfast buffet. Just down the road from the AC Mauro, where the staff (presumably used to Posh and Becks and not interested in lesser beings) couldn't have been more UNfriendly if they'd tried! There are trendier hotels, and more central (as in, close to the museums) hotels, but this is a good one, very friendly, and only a few minutes from the shops of the Salamanca district, or the round-town tour buses. Would stay again. 
